{| class="infobox" style="width: 20em; float:right; clear:right; font-size:90%" cellspacing="4" |- style="vertical-align: top;" ! colspan="2" style="text-align: center;" | <big>'''[[Live Earth]]'''</big> |- style="vertical-align: top;" | colspan="2" style="text-align: center;" | <!-- Image with inadequate rationale removed: [[Image:Live Earth Logo.png|230px|The Live Earth logo representing the "[[Save Our Selves|S.O.S.]]" message.]] --> |- style="vertical-align: top;" | colspan="2" style="text-align: center;" | [[Image:Live Earth - Rio de Janeiro.svg|230px|The Live Earth Rio de Janeiro.]] |- style="vertical-align: top;" | colspan="2" style="text-align: center;" | <small>Rio de Janeiro Concert location</small> |- style="vertical-align: top;" | '''Location''' || [[Copacabana, Rio de Janeiro|Copacabana Beach]], [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]] |- style="vertical-align: top;" | '''Founded by''' || [[Al Gore]] and [[Kevin Wall]] |- style="vertical-align: top;" | '''Date''' || July 7, 2007 |- style="vertical-align: top;" | '''Genre(s)''' || [[pop music|Pop]] and [[Rock music]] |- style="vertical-align: top;" | '''Website''' || [http://liveearth.msn.com/concerts/brazil Live Earth Brazil Site] |}
The '''[[Live Earth]] concert for [[South America]]''' was held at [[Copacabana, Rio de Janeiro|Copacabana Beach]], [[Rio de Janeiro]], [[Brazil]], on July 7, 2007. It is one of two free Live Earth concerts, the other being held in [[Live Earth concert, Washington, D.C.|Washington, D.C.]] It was the last concert to start during the day-long event. However, that didn't make it the last to finish, for the [[Live Earth concert, New York City|New York]] concert was still going on when things wrapped up in Rio. [[Lenny Kravitz]] was the headliner, playing a free gig there for the second time.
A few days before the event, a State prosecutor tried to cancel it, due to an alleged lack of police personnel to take care of security. However, the day after that, the concert was reinstated.<ref>[http://uk.news.yahoo.com/rtrs/20070706/ten-uk-concert-rio-3334b85.html Rio Live Earth to go on after ban revoked] Yahoo News</ref> Attendance was of about 400,000 people,<ref name="attendance">{{cite news | url = http://rjtv.globo.com/Jornalismo/RJTV/0,,MUL136671-9097,00.html | title = 400 mil contra o aquecimento | publisher = ''[[Rede Globo|RJTV]]'' | date = 2007-07-09 | accessdate = 2008-04-13 | language = Portuguese}}</ref> much less than the crowd drawn to [[Copacabana (Rio de Janeiro)|Copacabana]] by the [[A Bigger Bang Tour|Rolling Stones free concert]] on February 18, 2006, which exceeded a million people.<ref name="stones">{{cite news | url = http://rjtv.globo.com/Jornalismo/RJTV/0,,MUL126590-9097,00.html | publisher = ''[[Rede Globo|RJTV]]'' | language = Portuguese | accessdate = 2008-04-13 | date = 2006-02-20 | title = Noite no Rio}}</ref> Audience numbers were closer to those of the other [[Lenny Kravitz]] performance there, on March 21, 2005. On that occasion, [[Lenny Kravitz|Kravitz]] performed for 300,000{{Citation needed|date=July 2007}} people, in a concert of his own, staged at a different location on the beach. The [[Rolling Stones]] concert and Live Earth happened at exactly the same spot, in front of the [[Copacabana Palace]] hotel.
