[[Image:Onzelievehereboom.jpg|thumb|The Onzelievehereboom before its felling by a storm.]]
'''Onzelievehereboom''' was the name of a 1200-year-old [[oak tree]] in [[Kortessem]], Belgium, dedicated by popular piety to ''Onze Lieve Here'', "Our Dear Lord". It was believed to be the [[List of oldest trees|oldest tree]] in [[Belgium]] when it was overthrown by a storm 18 July 2009.
